'Iia' is a village in Kõpu Parish, Viljandi County in Estonia. As of 2011
Census, the settlement's population was 23.<ref name=2011census></ref>

The northern half of the village's territory is covered by the Ördi bog, which
is located in the Soomaa National Park.
